            <div type="apparatus">
                <listApp>
                    <app>
                        <note xml:id="Job-016-fn1" type="footnote">JSul.I.04: The Karaim equivalent
                            of the standard Hebrew Job 16:1 is not included in the text, probably
                            intentionally, see Job 3:1, 4:1, etc. for similar cases. The text is
                            reconstructed here on the basis of ADub.III.84. The Hebrew text is not
                            omitted, see BHeb. <foreign xml:lang="he" style="unicode-bidi: embed;"
                                >וַיַּעַן אִיֹּוב וַיֹּאמַר </foreign>
                            ‘Then Job answered and said’ (Job 16:1). | C: <emph>Da ǯoɣap berdi Ijov
                                da ajtty</emph>. | QB: <emph>Da ǯoɣap berdi Ijov da ajtty</emph>. |
                            ADub.III.84: <emph>Da qaruv berdi Ijov da ajtty</emph>. | Kobeckaitė
                            (2019): <emph>Da qaruv berdi Ijov da ajtty</emph>.</note>
                        <note xml:id="Job-016-fn2" type="footnote">A North-Western Karaim form (cf.
                            SWKar. <emph>mana</emph> &amp;lt; MWKar. *<emph>maŋa </emph>&amp;gt;
                            NWKar. <emph>maja</emph>) the use of which suggests that the translator
                            or the copyist availed himself of translations written in that
                            particular dialect. See also Job 19:3, 19:19, 19:21, 20:2, 20:3,
                            30:1.</note>
                    </app>
                </listApp>
            </div>
